  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6577.89 sitting below the GEX flip at 6592, dealers are currently in supportive mode as they're long gamma and will buy any dips toward the 6550 negative gamma wall. The massive positive gamma concentration from 6580-6600 (especially the 26.9B wall at 6600) creates a strong magnetic pull that should limit upside breakouts, while the recent GEX surge indicates fresh positioning that reinforces these stabilizing dynamics. Key levels to watch are 6550 downside support where dealers accelerate buying and 6600 resistance where dealer selling intensifies.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get pulled back toward the 6580-6600 range with limited breakout potential.",
